## Attribution

This project is built upon Vercel's Next.js WordPress CMS example, which is part
of the Next.js repository (https://github.com/vercel/next.js). The original
example provided the foundation for WordPress GraphQL integration.

The following significant enhancements were added by MalTar Designs:
- Advanced BlockRenderer system for Gutenberg and ACF blocks
- Comprehensive testing suite with Jest and Playwright
- Production-ready security features and webhook system
- Enhanced TypeScript configuration and type safety
- Tailwind CSS 4 integration with shadcn/ui components
- Advanced SEO and metadata generation
- Client-focused documentation and deployment automation
- Performance optimizations and bundle analysis
- Professional development workflow and tooling

These enhancements represent substantial new work and intellectual property
developed by MalTar Designs for the benefit of the WordPress and Next.js
community.